ExecDesc.value: Oracle Outside In JPEG 2000 QCD Segment Processing Heap Buffer Overflow

EngDesc.value: A heap buffer overflow vulnerability exists in Oracle Outside-In, a set of libraries used to decode many file formats.The vulnerability exists when handling the QCD segments in JPEG 2000 files. Oracle Outside-In is embedded in many enterprise applications.This vulnerability can be exploited by causing an application that uses the vulnerable library to handle a malformed JPEG 2000 file. Depending on the application, user interaction may be required. Successful exploitation can result in arbitrary code execution in the context of the affected application.
